OL,3,CFormer PM Gordon Brown calls on Labour
OL,4,Cto scrap two-child benefit cap
OL,6,FBrown, who also served as Chancellor
OL,7,Ffor a decade under Tony Blair's
OL,8,Fgovernment, believes that by scrapping
OL,9,Fthe cap the government "can take
OL,10,F500,000 children out of poverty".
OL,12,F"This can be done without breaking any
OL,13,Ffiscal rules or without having to
OL,14,Fbreak manifesto commitments," he added.
OL,16,FTo cover the estimated #3 billion it
OL,17,Fwould cost to scrap it, he's proposed
OL,18,Ffunding measures including an online
OL,19,Fgambling tax, a levy on commercial
OL,20,Fbanks and a change to gift aid rules
OL,21,Ffor higher rate taxpayers.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/19
